          },
          "datePublished": "2020-11-25",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "A school that asks for parents to teach in school,wherein,such teachers and students will be bestowed with special ‘status’-making them eligible for everything,panning from the special attention of fellow teachers,special gestures from school,nominations as heads of various clubs to many ‘firsts’ in school competitions,none of which are deserving.So if you are a parent otherwise free,please sign up as a teacher to avail all the above said privileges.And to those who care about real education,focusing on the overall development of your child, get ready to be agitated from day 1.Lastly,to the students who really possess some talent or good in what you do,please don’t expect anything from the school,they won’t even notice you.This school is for inane and flippant,vocal braggarts and regressive ‘staff Caucus’ - and the centrepiece of this drama is a revolving door of principals, who are, in turn, often bootlicked and influenced.\nHaving witnessed everything,the only few teachers who really know their job,make their imminent exit ,as the ‘caucus’ flourishes like the water weed Salvinia Molesta,by receiving awards and recognitions from the management.\n\nPositively, if the child is intelligent enough,they can get accustomed with a future hypocrite society where good is never recognised and evil is being nurtured by the system itself.\n\nAll the best parents and children.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
